  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this activity is for students to create a rectangle with a given area. Students use what they know about area and the structure of rectangles to decide on the side lengths of the rectangle. Students use tape (painter's or masking) to create the rectangles. They should have enough tape to create square feet within the rectangle, but should be encouraged to mark the 1 foot intervals to help them visualize the square feet inside the rectangle, if needed.</p>
<p>In the synthesis, each group shares strategies for creating a rectangle and how they know the area is the given number of square feet.</p>
<p>When students think about the structure of a rectangle and use it to create a rectangle with a given area they are looking for and making use of structure (MP7).</p>
  </paragraphs>


